The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 February is 38,354 (4,439.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 February, there were 1,384 new confirmed cases (160.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 January, there were 2,180 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 37% (796 fewer cases).
